  "experimental_data": {
    "gel_layer_pH": "Measured hourly for 8h using contact pH electrode. At pH1.2, all samples pH 1.23-1.65. After change to pH6.8, sample R pH 6.54-6.76; acid-containing samples maintained lower pH. Citric acid samples showed sharp pH increase after 360 min due to complete leaching.",
    "statistical_analysis": {
      "full_factorial": "Concentration of pH modifier (p<0.01) and type (p<0.05) significantly affected drug release and surface pH at 360 and 480 min.",
      "PLS_2_regression": "First two PLS components explained 75% (X-data) and 73% (Y-data) variation. Concentration (p<0.01) positively correlated with drug release, negatively with pH at 360 min. pKa (p<0.01) crucial for drug release and pH at 360 min. Solubility only affected pH at 480 min (p<0.05)."
    },
